security_findings.evidence:
Unpatched wil_details_FeatureReporting_ReportUsageToServiceDirect (sub_1C00016D4) reads the WIL feature-property cache via a module-global:
  int32_t* r = wil_details_FeatureReporting_RecordUsageInCache (sub_1c00013fc)(&var_50, off_1C00038F8, arg3, arg2 >> 0x20);
  int64_t cb = g_wil_details_recordFeatureUsage;  // set-once callback pointer (data_1c0004170)
  if (cb)
      __guard_dispatch_icall(cb, 0x3a6cba9, arg3, 1, off_1C00038F8, &var_38);  // CFG-checked dispatch

Patched wil_details_FeatureReporting_ReportUsageToServiceDirect (sub_1400018DC) (newer WIL: state from context):
  uint64_t sub_1400018dc(void* ctx, ...) {
      int32_t* state = *(ctx + 8);  // caller-supplied context, not off_1C00038F8
      wil_details_FeatureReporting_IncrementUsageInCache (sub_1400016bc)(state, rsi, arg3, &s);
      // g_wil_details_recordFeatureUsage is STILL read as a module-global here
  }

Unpatched wil_InitializeFeatureStaging (sub_1C000B008): calls PopulateInitialConfiguredFeatureStates and EvaluateFeatureDependencies, then registers the change notification only if a feature descriptor requests it. It allocates nothing and inserts nothing into a list (no ImpAddAllowListEvent call).

Patched wil_InitializeFeatureStaging (sub_14000CB94): adds the standard one-time-init guard (g_wil_details_isFeatureStagingInitialized at 0x14000CBAA/0x14000CBB8), sets g_wil_details_recordFeatureUsage at 0x14000CC70, and adds a new RtlRegisterFeatureUsageProvider registration at 0x14000CCB4 — newer-WIL library shape, not a security fix.

Unpatched wil_InitializeFeatureStaging (sub_1C000B008) — allocates nothing, no list insertion:
  RtlQueryFeatureConfigurationChangeStamp();
  wil_details_PopulateInitialConfiguredFeatureStates();
  wil_details_EvaluateFeatureDependencies();
  // scans wil_details_featureDescriptors; registers ONLY if a descriptor requests notification
  RtlRegisterFeatureConfigurationChangeNotification(wil_details_ReevaluateOnFeatureConfigurationChange, 0, &stamp, &wil_details_featureChangeNotification);

Patched wil_InitializeFeatureStaging (sub_14000CB94) — adds one-time-init guard + new usage provider:
  if (g_wil_details_isFeatureStagingInitialized) return;   // 0x14000CBAA
  g_wil_details_isFeatureStagingInitialized = 1;            // 0x14000CBB8
  ... same Populate/Evaluate/RegisterChangeNotification ...
  g_wil_details_recordFeatureUsage = wil_details_RecordFeatureUsageReporting;  // 0x14000CC70
  RtlRegisterFeatureUsageProvider(...);                     // 0x14000CCB4 (new WIL surface)
